Package com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.oracle.abstraction

Interface Summary
IVisitable Implementors of this interface use the visitor pattern for oracles.
 

Class Summary
Oracle Represents a test case oracle - that is, a set of constraints on post-state of a program following the execution of a test case.
OracleAssertion An OracleAssertion is a set of OracleExpression instances.
OracleComparator Provides a high-level representation of a comparator.
OracleConstraint An OracleConstraint is a set of assertions which must hold for the poststate of the system under test, in order for the testcase to be considered a success.
OracleExpression Represents a boolean expression in a constraint on the post-state of a system.
OracleLiteral Represents, loosely, a literal in a FOL formula, which may be either a variable or a constant.
OracleMetaExtractor This visitor is used in order to extract metadata about the poststate of a program, as represented by its postcondition.
OracleMethodInvocation Represents a method invocation in an oracle.
OracleOperator Represents an operator as part of an oracle.
OracleQuantifier Represents a quantifier in an oracle expression, semantically equivalent to the same construct in a FOL formula.
OracleType Represents the types of elements in an Oracle.
 

Enum Summary
OracleComparator.ComparatorType The types of Java comparators.
OracleOperator.OperatorType The type of the operators in oracles.
OracleQuantifier.QuantifierType The possible types of quantifiers.
